The paper deals with the uplink of massive multicell multiple-input multiple-output systems, which involves wireless communication, signal processing, and resource allocation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of massive arrays and the detection of signals from multiple terminals, which are relevant to the categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.COM (Computers and Society). The proposed resource allocation scheme involves selecting the training duration and power, which are related to network protocols and optimization, and thus the paper may also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
